utility

Interface MyBSTreeADT<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of elements this tree holds.
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public interface MyBSTreeADT<E>
extends java.io.Serializable

    The BSTreeADT interface is designed to be used as a binary search tree structure. This structure maintains data in an ordered tree. The implementors of this interface will be required to add all the functionality.

    Author:
    Ivan Okhrimovich

      • add

      • remove

        E remove(E toRemove)
        Removes a value which equals to the indicated value. Only one value is removed, and no guarantee is given on which of duplicate values will be removed. Value returned is no longer part of the structure.
        Parameters:
        toRemove - Value to be removed from this tree.
        Returns:
        Actual value removed from this tree, or null if the tree does not contain the specified value.

      • contains

        boolean contains(E toFind)
        Determines if the binary search tree contains a value. Returns true if this tree contains the specified value.
        Parameters:
        toFind - The value whose presence in this tree is to be tested.
        Returns:
        true if this tree contains the specified value.

      • clear
